               <p>633. 
               
                  <persName id="t18000917-46-defend438" type="defendantName">
                     THOMAS 
                     CHALFONT
                  <interp inst="t18000917-46-defend438" type="surname" value="CHALFONT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-46-defend438" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-46-defend438" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-46-defend438" type="age" value="17"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18000917-46-off240" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18000917-46-off240" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18000917-46-off240" type="offenceSubcategory" value="mail"></interp>
               that he, being a person <rs id="t18000917-46-deflabel241" type="occupation">employed in the General Post-office</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000917-46-defend438 t18000917-46-deflabel241"></join>, on the <rs id="t18000917-46-cd242" type="crimeDate">18th of April</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000917-46-off240 t18000917-46-cd242"></join>, feloniously did secrete a letter, or packet, directed to Messrs. Bedwells, St. John's-street, and stealing thereout a Banbury Bank-note, value 1ol. the property of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18000917-46-victim440" type="victimName">
                           Bernard 
                           Bedwell
                        <interp inst="t18000917-46-victim440" type="surname" value="Bedwell"></interp>
